OL,3,CWhat security do MPs have?
OL,5,FWords by Emily Youlton, Senior
OL,6,FPolitics Producer
OL,8,FCounter terrorism police have taken
OL,9,Fover the murder investigation into the
OL,10,Fdeath of Ann Widdecombe, once again
OL,11,Fraising questions about the safety and
OL,12,Fsecurity of politicians.
OL,14,FSpeaker of the House of Commons, Sir
OL,15,FLindsay Hoyle, has insisted that all
OL,16,FMPs who raise security concerns are
OL,17,Ftreated equally, stressing that "there
OL,18,Fis no difference between any member".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784063895
OL,3,CWhat security do MPs have?
OL,5,FHe said that whenever concerns are
OL,6,Fbrought to his attention, MPs can be
OL,7,Freassured that they are "passed on to
OL,8,Fthe security people to deal with".
OL,10,FHis comments come after criticism from
OL,11,FReform UK, whose home affairs
OL,12,Fspokesperson, Zia Yusuf, claimed that
OL,13,FMPs in his party were not being given
OL,14,Fprotection.
OL,16,FWiddecombe, a former Conservative
OL,17,Fminister and later a Reform
OL,18,Fspokeswoman, was found dead at her
OL,19,Fhome in Haytor on Dartmoor on
OL,20,FThursday, having sustained serious
OL,21,Finjuries.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784063895
OL,3,CWhat security do MPs have?
OL,5,FOn Sunday, Yusuf wrote on social media
OL,6,Fthat "none of the Government, the
OL,7,FSpeaker, nor the police care at all
OL,8,Fabout the security of Reform MPs" and
OL,9,Fclaimed that several had asked for
OL,10,Fhelp but did not receive a response.
OL,12,FHoyle appeared to reject this claim on
OL,13,FMonday, when he told MPs: "Every
OL,14,Fmember of Parliament is equal in their
OL,15,Fsecurity to me ` there is no
OL,16,Fdifference between any member, I want
OL,17,Fto reassure you."
OL,19,FSo what security do MPs actually get,
OL,20,Fand who is responsible for keeping
OL,21,Fthem safe? ITV News explains.
OL,26,@nD@FOUpD@aO]uD@[OU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/22
