CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784063895
OL,3,CWhat security do MPs have?
OL,5,FBut this issue does not exclude men.
OL,6,FDoncaster East MP Lee Pitcher has
OL,7,Fpreviously told ITV News that he is
OL,8,F"hugely conscious, almost obsessively"
OL,9,Fabout security, and worries not just
OL,10,Fabout himself but also his team and
OL,11,Ffamily.
OL,13,FPitcher has installed panic alarms at
OL,14,Fhome, and his kitchen window was
OL,15,Frecently smashed. Although he doesn't
OL,16,Fknow what happened, he said it looked
OL,17,Flike a "rifle shot".
OL,19,FWho is responsible for MP safety?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30613
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784063895
OL,3,CWhat security do MPs have?
OL,5,FMPs' roles are not just confined to
OL,6,Fone place; they work across the
OL,7,Fparliamentary estate and out in their
OL,8,Fconstituencies, meaning several
OL,9,Forganisations are involved in keeping
OL,10,Fthem safe.
OL,12,FWhen MPs are in Westminster, on the
OL,13,Fparliamentary estate, the
OL,14,FParliamentary Security Department
OL,15,F(PSD) has overall responsibility for
OL,16,Fkeeping them safe; this includes
OL,17,Fpoliticians in the House of Lords, too.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30614
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784063895
OL,3,CWhat security do MPs have?
OL,5,FThe PSD also works with the
OL,6,FMetropolitan Police, which assigns
OL,7,Fpolice officers to parliament, as well
OL,8,Fas a special team based in Westminster
OL,9,Fcalled the Parliamentary Liaison and
OL,10,FInvestigation Team (PLaIT).
OL,12,FThe job of PLaIT is to work with
OL,13,Fpolice forces across the country to
OL,14,Fensure MP safety and coordinate with
OL,15,Fthe PSD in Westminster.
OL,17,FThe Speaker of the House of Commons is
OL,18,Falso involved in looking after MPs'
OL,19,Fsafety, seen as the leader of MPs and
OL,20,Ftheir conduct.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30615
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784063895
OL,3,CWhat security do MPs have?
OL,5,FSpeaking to ITV News earlier this
OL,6,Fyear, on the anniversary of Jo Cox's
OL,7,Fmurder, the Speaker said: "There's
OL,8,Fonly one thing that keeps me awake at
OL,9,Fnight, and that's the safety and
OL,10,Fsecurity of MPs."
OL,12,FWhen MPs are out in their
OL,13,Fconstituencies, responsibility for
OL,14,Ftheir safety relies on the local
OL,15,Fpolice force, acting alongside the PSD
OL,16,Fand PLaIT.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30616
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784063895
OL,3,CWhat security do MPs have?
OL,5,FFollowing the murder of Cox in 2016, a
OL,6,Fprogramme called Operation Bridger was
OL,7,Festablished to enhance MP safety, and
OL,8,Fincludes measures like every MP having
OL,9,Fa named contact in their local police
OL,10,Fforce to help deal with security
OL,11,Fissues.
OL,13,FThis was later extended in 2024 to
OL,14,Finclude all candidates in general
OL,15,Felections as well as local officials,
OL,16,Fsuch as councillors, mayors and police
OL,17,Fand crime commissioners.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30617
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784063895
OL,3,CWhat security do MPs have?
OL,5,FMany MPs have security guards,
OL,6,Fparticularly when hosting their
OL,7,Fconstituency surgeries, a chance for
OL,8,Flocal people to raise concerns with
OL,9,Fthem.
OL,11,FWhat security measures can MPs receive?
OL,13,FSecurity for MPs is divided into two
OL,14,Fcategories: routine and enhanced.
OL,16,FThe IfG describes routine security as
OL,17,Fmeasures for all MPs, and enhanced
OL,18,Fsecurity measures are those
OL,19,Frecommended by the police to certain
OL,20,FMPs depending on their circumstances.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30618
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784063895
OL,3,CWhat security do MPs have?
OL,5,FSince the murder of David Amess in
OL,6,F2021 - who was fatally stabbed during
OL,7,Fa constituency surgery in 2021 - MPs
OL,8,Fhave been offered private security
OL,9,Fguards at surgeries.
OL,11,FSeparately, ministers and Secretaries
OL,12,Fof State may receive security guards
OL,13,Ffrom the Home Office, usually on the
OL,14,Fadvice of a departmental security
OL,15,Fadvisor or at their own request.
OL,17,FAs expected, the prime minister, home
OL,18,Fsecretary and defence secretary are
OL,19,Fall given state-funded protection and
OL,20,Farmed bodyguards.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30619
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784063895
OL,3,CWhat security do MPs have?
OL,5,FSome politicians in the UK, such as
OL,6,FNigel Farage, cover their own security
OL,7,Fcosts or rely on private funding
OL,8,Frather than state-provided protection.
OL,10,FThe i Paper revealed that the Reform
OL,11,FUK leader was offered public
OL,12,Fprotection but declined it as he
OL,13,Fconsidered it to be inadequate.
OL,15,FThe package he was offered would be
OL,16,Fsimilar to that of Conservative leader
OL,17,FKemi Badenoch, but he felt his package
OL,18,Fhad been downgraded.
OL,20,FHe has previously said he is the most
OL,21,Fthreatened politician in the UK.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30620
SC,0020
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784063895
OL,3,CWhat security do MPs have?
OL,5,FSenior figures in Reform have
OL,6,Fcomplained about the level of security
OL,7,Ftheir party and its leader have been
OL,8,Foffered.
OL,10,FOn Monday, Home Secretary Shabana
OL,11,FMahmood offered Farage a meeting with
OL,12,Fthe chairperson of the Royal and VIP
OL,13,FExecutive Committee (Ravec).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G20/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30621
SC,0021
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784063895
OL,3,CWhat security do MPs have?
OL,5,FRavec is an independent body within
OL,6,Fthe Home Office that is typically
OL,7,Fresponsible for security measures for
OL,8,Fhigh-profile people, including
OL,9,Fcelebrities, royals and politicians.
OL,10,FIn recent years, its remit has
OL,11,Fexpanded to include MPs, even ones
OL,12,Fwithout a presumed high profile.
OL,14,FFarage has thanked the Home Secretary
OL,15,Fin a post on X and said: "I will meet
OL,16,Fwith the chair of Ravec and discuss
OL,17,Fthe security of all Reform
OL,18,Fpoliticians, including those who are
OL,19,Fnot MPs".
